(thirdQuint)The Effect of Bronchodilator on Eosinophilic Bronchitis and Cough Variant Asthma.

 Study groups: 45 patients with chronic cough will be collected and two groups will formed based on diagnosis as follows: Group 1: EB group The patients with eosinophilic bronchitis received Bambuterol Hydrochloride tablets 10mg Q24 for three days .

 Group 2: CVA group The patients with cough variant asthma received Bambuterol Hydrochloride tablets 10mg Q24 for three days .

 Observe the response to Bambuterol Hydrochloride tablets treatment three days later and compare the effective rate of patients with EB and CVA.

 Then the study will be over.

